<TITLE> Hazari refused bail, sent to jail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Hazari refused bail, sent to jail Dhaka, Apr 15 (bdnews24.com)Former lawmaker Joynal Hazari was sent to jail as he surrendered to the court Wednesday. The expelled Awami League leader, once known as a notorious Feni 'crime figure', appeared at the court premises accompanied by hundreds of activists and supporters who chanting slogans. He went the before district and sessions judge, additional district and sessions judge, chief judicial magistrate and senior judicial magistrate requesting bail in six different cases. He received bail in five cases, including a murder case and three involving charges of 'oppression' or 'violence', but the senior judicial magistrate refused him bail in the sixth case involving money laundering charges and ordered him behind bars. "Many conspiracies have been hatched against me in the past, but to no effect," Hazari told a gathering of supporters on the court premises before being sent to jail,. "I went into hiding in 2001 only to save my life  I was an elected MP thrice. But now I am being harassed," he said. He urged all to "have patience in the face of all oddities". b
